VALUES ('B2_U1_B2_I1', 'ingles-b2-U1', 6, 'multiple_choice_cloze', 'Fill in the blanks with the correct idiomatic expression from the options provided.', '{"prompt_es":"Fill in the blanks with the correct idiomatic expression from the options provided.","mastery_tag":"vocabulary:b2-idiomatic","main_text":"Understanding idiomatic expressions can greatly enhance your language skills. Here are some sentences with gaps to complete:\n\n1. He really gave me the [GAP 1] when I asked to borrow his car. (1)[GAP 2]\n\n2. Don''t worry about the presentation; just go with the [GAP 3]. (2)[GAP 4]\n\n3. She’s really [GAP 5] to her work and often stays late. (3)[GAP 6]\n\n4. After a long day, I like to kick back and [GAP 7]. (4)[GAP 8]\n\n5. They had a [GAP 9] of a time at the party last night! (5)[GAP 10]","gaps":[{"id":"1","options":[{"id":"o1","text":"green light"},{"id":"o2","text":"cold shoulder"},{"id":"o3","text":"red flag"},{"id":"o4","text":"blue sky"}]},{"id":"2","options":[{"id":"o1","text":"flow"},{"id":"o2","text":"line"},{"id":"o3","text":"road"},{"id":"o4","text":"way"}]},{"id":"3","options":[{"id":"o1","text":"devoted"},{"id":"o2","text":"dedicated"},{"id":"o3","text":"committed"},{"id":"o4","text":"attached"}]},{"id":"4","options":[{"id":"o1","text":"chill"},{"id":"o2","text":"sit"},{"id":"o3","text":"sleep"},{"id":"o4","text":"work"}]},{"id":"5","options":[{"id":"o1","text":"blast"},{"id":"o2","text":"breeze"},{"id":"o3","text":"storm"},{"id":"o4","text":"quake"}]}],"correct_answer":{"1":"o2","2":"o1","3":"o2","4":"o1","5":"o1"},"explanation":"(1) La expresión ''cold shoulder'' significa ignorar a alguien o no mostrar interés en algo. En este contexto, se refiere a que alguien no está dispuesto a prestar su coche.\n(2) La expresión ''go with the flow'' se refiere a aceptar las cosas como vienen y no resistirse a las circunstancias.\n(3) La palabra ''dedicated'' implica una fuerte devoción o compromiso hacia algo, en este caso, el trabajo.\n(4) La expresión ''kick